Sentencas: Performance and stability of five cermet-supported button-type solid oxide fuel cells featuring a bilayered electrolyte (SSZ/SDC).
Titulo: Stability study of cermet-supported solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layered electrolyte

Sentencas: an SSC cathode, and a Ni-SSZ anode, were analyzed using polarization curves, impedance spectroscopy, and post-mortem SEM observation.
Titulo: Stability study of cermet-supported solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layered electrolyte

Sentencas: The cell performance degradation at 650 degrees C in H-2/air both with and without DC bias conditions was manifested primarily as an increase in polarization resistance, approximately at a rate of 2.3 m Omega cm(2) h(-1) at OCV, suggesting a decrease in electrochemical kinetics as the main phenomenon responsible for the performance decay.
Titulo: Stability study of cermet-supported solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layered electrolyte

Sentencas: In addition, the initial series resistance was about ten times higher than the calculated resistance corresponding to the electrolyte, reflecting a possible inter-reaction between the electrolyte layers that occurred during the sintering stage.
Titulo: Stability study of cermet-supported solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layered electrolyte

Sentencas: In situ and ex situ sintered cathodes showed no obvious difference in cell performance or decay rate.
Titulo: Stability study of cermet-supported solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layered electrolyte

Sentencas: The stability of the cells with and without electrical load was also investigated and no significant influence of DC bias was recorded.
Titulo: Stability study of cermet-supported solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layered electrolyte

Sentencas: Based on the experimental results presented, we preliminarily attribute the performance degradation to electrochemical and microstructural degradation of the cathode.
Titulo: Stability study of cermet-supported solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layered electrolyte
